parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Tire Failure Due to Manufacturing Defects
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire failure can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
Improper tire balancing and alignment can cause uneven tire wear, vibration, and reduced vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents.
Failure to maintain proper tire pressure, rotate tires, and check alignment can lead to premature tire wear, reduced vehicle control, and increased risk of accidents.
The sudden and unexpected closure of the hood can cause serious injury or death to individuals working under the hood, and may also cause damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: The hood suddenly falls and slams closed
with a higher likelihood of occurrence in cooler temperatures.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The paint defects and flaking can lead to rust and corrosion, compromising the vehicle's structural integrity and affecting its overall appearance.
symptoms: The paint scratches and flakes off easily

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The casting defect in the wheels can cause cracks to develop, leading to wheel failure, loss of control, and increased risk of accidents.
The sudden failure of the front strut spring can cause loss of steering control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when traveling at high speeds.
symptoms: broken spring end piercing into the tire

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Tire Failure due to Strut Spring Breakage
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the strut spring can cause tire blowouts, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
The faulty throttle chamber can cause the vehicle to hesitate or stall when accelerating from a stopped position, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The gas pedal is slow to respond
the vehicle hesitates or stalls when accelerating from a stopped position
the vehicle lurches forward when more force is applied to the gas pedal
